  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nOn Grafana instance of my node I can observe strange behavior of JsonRpc statistics.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43241881/209152902-f5892173-59ae-4c03-91aa-d5f3f4961bd4.png)\r\n\r\nOn Image above I can see that in 5 minutes slot I have ~150 requests per second but below one (total) is showing huge numbers which totally not match requests sent during 5 minutes slot.\r\nWhen I increase slot to 15 minutes it is increasing so it is not \"total\" for whole node lifecycle but total for selected period of time.\r\n\r\nI had about 5-10 jsonrpc errors in 5 minutes but chart is telling about 39k of errors which can't be right.\r\n\r\n@asdacap Had some idea but still it wasn't accurate enough so maybe metric itself is broken and needs to be revisited and adjusted.\r\n\r\nINFO:\r\nIt happens on every node so no specific node is needed for reproduction.",
